/locationNotes/%2Fteam%2Flocation%2Fa07a: {"type": "edit", "field": "information", "label": "Other info", "before": null, "after": "Adult NYC residents with a physical SSN, ID and a proof of address may qualify to get paid to donate plasma given they maintain multiple health requirements such as not being on certain medications, fore example PreP, have no random sexual partners, being HIV-negative and never have been diagnosed with Hepatitis C along with being clean from drugs and STI for certain periods prior to dotation. Walk in to get your veins checked out and see if you qualify. Individuals who have been permanently deferred from donating will be identified through a database. There are locations in all boroughs, except for Staten Island. {"type": "edit", "field": "description", "label": "Description", "before": "Female-identifying and non-binary individuals connected to Brooklyn can apply for the before October, 2024 for the following programs lasting the entire academic year:\\n\u2022 Young Women\u2019s Advisory Council (YWAC) see bit.ly/25YWAC (case-sensitive), ages 16-24\\n\u2022 Sisters In Strength (SIS), see bit.ly/25SIS (case-sensitive), ages 14-18 for individuals who have survived gender-based violence and their allies.\\nThe age and gender requirements are not extremely hard an alumni fellowshipis availableto aged-out participants. The same link will be used for the next cohort in September 2025.\\n$300 monthly stipend is offered contingent on biweekly attendance with additional paid opportunities. 1-2 a month meeting with a social worker is offered.
